About REESE'S
The original Reese's Peanut Butter Cup was created in 1928 as a partnership between H.B. Reese and Milton Hershey. Since then, the Reese's family has grown to include a variety of flavors and forms. Today, you can try Reese's products in dark chocolate, white chocolate, snack-sized pieces, and candy bars.

Reese's Peanut Butter Cups

The Perfect Combination

Nothing goes together better than creamy milk chocolate and Reese's Peanut Butter. Except maybe Reese's Peanut Butter Cups and your refrigerator. Start chilling out with the perfect combo, because no one should ever have to choose between delicious and perfection.
  • Reese's Candies are a classic candy collaboration; the perfect combination and chocolate and peanut butter
  • With two or more peanut butter cups per pack, sharing is easy, if you're into that
  • Gluten free and kosher
  • Reese's Peanut Butter Cups are the perfect companion for movies, sports, and parties
Read more

So many choices, so little time!




Sharing is Caring

You can easily take these treats to the office or a get-together with friends and still have plenty to stash in your freezer. As always, sharing is optional.

Bake with the Best

What's better than a chocolate chip cookie? A chocolate chip cookie and Reese's Peanut Butter Cup sandwich, that's what. So easy, you could make it in your sleep.

Pairs well with...Everything

We know you may not love going out, but Reese's Peanut Butter Cups are great wing-men. The perfect combination of chocolate and peanut butter is best enjoyed during parties, at the movies, sporting events, and more.

Important information

Safety Warning
When a product contains a major allergen, it is listed as an ingredient on our labels. We have strict procedures in place to prevent crossover of allergens into other products that do not contain the allergen. In instances where we have a concern about possible crossover of an allergen, such information will be placed on the label. You are advised to check the ingredient label on the package each time before you make a purchase, as recommended by Food Allergy and Anaphylaxis Network (FAAN).

3.0 out of 5 starsStick to the store
ByJustTrustMeon May 2, 2015
Size: 19.5 ounce|Verified Purchase
You really can't go wrong with some Reese's cups, but despite being shipped during winter, they were melted and gross looking with that effect of the oil rising to the surface or whatever it is that makes them look like the underside of a tentacle. They tasted okay, but even though I'm not squeamish, the look really detracted from the experience. I know some melting can be expected, but I've never had so many reese's look like this before. Stick to the store.

3.0 out of 5 starsGreat value but melted during shipping
ByBurhan Sandhuon November 14, 2015
Size: 1.5 ounce (pack of 36)|Verified Purchase
I love me a good Reese's any time of day, and I got a subscription to these since they were cheaper than forking a dollar over to the vending machine every time I was craving a peanut butter cup. I got my first order this week, and while they taste just like any Reese's peanut butter cup ought to, they did arrive pretty deformed since they melted and cooled during shipping (see picture). I didn't have an expiration date issue as mentioned in other reviews-- mine were all best by October 2016, a year from now.

I'm following up with Amazon to see if I can get some kind of refrigerated shipping, and I'll update this review if there's any progress on future orders.

3.0 out of 5 starsNot Too Impressed, But Worth The Price
ByMRon April 10, 2012
Size: 2.8 ounce( pack of 24)|Verified Purchase
Local grocery and convenience stores sell Reese's peanut butter cups for about $1 for a two-pack. So when I saw that they were on sale here on Amazon for less than $1 each for packs of four, I was thrilled. However, the feeling has since eroded after noticing a couple of issues:

1) Another reviewer said that the candy comes nearly stale, and I have to agree partially. The packages are almost expired (in just 6 months), but from what I can tell, the taste still seems OK (for me).

2) There is weird condensation on each peanut butter cup. This is strange because where I am now there is super low humidity (just 26% with fire watches). So I am not sure where the condensation came from but the box does say to store in a cool DRY place.

Other than those two things, I cautiously tried a taste test and they do seem OK. If you are looking for ultra-fresh, you may be better off shopping somewhere local. But if you'll give these away or your family goes through them fast, then maybe it's worth the low price. I don't think I will buy again, though.

5.0 out of 5 starsBest when ordered during colder months
ByArchie77on May 5, 2013
Size: 19.5 ounce (pack of 3)|Verified Purchase
The chocolate and peanut butter combination of these chocolates makes for a great tasting snack. However, keep in mind that your order may take days or weeks to arrive. During that time, chocolates such as these are subject melting due to heat.

I first ordered these a few years ago. The first time I ordered them, they arrived fairly deformed as they had melted during shipping. To me this wasn't a big issue, except that some of the chocolate had melted around the black paper wrapping that is around the chocolate cups, so I had to carefully peel the paper out from along the edges of the chocolate. While it was a slight added inconvenience, the chocolate still tasted the same which is what really matters.

The second time I ordered this product during the colder month of October. The chocolates arrived in perfect condition. For this reason, I would suggest ordering these during the colder months as they provide a sort of natural refrigeration during shipping.

Also as a quick tip, I've noticed that these tend to go on sale a few weeks before Halloween (this has been true for the last 2 years at least). I would recommend checking back for this product then (I believe last year they cost me just above $12).

These chocolates are really very delicious. I would recommend them if you're a fan of both milk chocolate and peanut butter.
